 challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nLocated east of downtown Bellevue, Wilburton Hill Park is a small park, but quite wooded and rugged for its size, with an extensive trail network – and a very cool pedestrian suspension bridge! Courses will be standard point-to-point, and Course 4 will be a combination of Courses 2 and 3, with a map exchange in between.","external_links":[{"link_url":"https://goo.gl/maps/AAEffUVadrp","link_type":"directions"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/event/wednesday-evening-1-2/","link_type":"event_page"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/map/wilburton-park/","link_type":"map"},{"link_url":"http://rg.cascadeoc.org/rg2/#179","link_type":"routegadget"},{"link_url":"https://cascadeoc.org/series/wednesday-evening/","link_type":"series"},{"link_url":"http://obasen.orientering.se/winsplits/online/en/default.asp?page=classes&databaseId=49058","link_type":"splits"}],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Designer","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7530-b85a-103e52302ff8","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Will Enger","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Epunch Coordinator","individual_id":"019d0a11-4d2f-736d-863f-5e546e61e969","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Ing Uhlin","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://cascadeoc.org/result/wes-1-wilburton-hill-park/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Welcome to our new meet director Morgan Cowper!\nThank You to all our Volunteers!\n\nThe first event in the 2017 Wednesday Evening Series will be held on World Orienteering Day! The Wednesday Evening Series is our most relaxed, casual set of navigation events, held in local parks once the weather warms up. These events are a little more low-key than those in the WIOL/Winter Series, and we always offer a barbeque afterward for all participants. Decompress after work, with or without your coworkers. Or meet your family at the park and enjoy a night off from cooking. Or meet a bunch of friends at the park for an evening of exploring together, chatting over some food, and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nLocated east of downtown Bellevue, Wilburton Hill Park is a small park, but quite wooded and rugged for its size, with an extensive trail network – and a very cool pedestrian suspension bridge! Courses will be standard point-to-point, and Course 4 will be a combination of Courses 2 and 3, with a map exchange in between."}
